PUSISIT.definition: to squirt, spurt water or other liquid substance, Agpusisit diay gripo.

PUSKOL.eng_example: That book which you are reading is thick.

PUSTA.definition: to make a bet, place a bet.

PUTAR.eng_example: Construct something where we are going to stay. 2. to invent, create.

PUTAR.definition: not completely made, incompletely made (e.g. a window, door, house).

PUTED.definition: a piece, a part of something.
to cut a part off, to shorten.

PUTIPOT.eng_example: Wind this string around that post.
PUTIPOT.ilok_example: Iputipot mo daytoy tali dita adigi.

PUTIPOT.eng_example: Wind a string around this post.

PUTO.definition: a kind of soft rice cake.

PUTONG.definition: to isolate, separate from the rest.

PUTPUT.definition: to do completely or thoroughly, to finish.
to make a sound like that of a horn.

PUYAT.definition: to stay awake late in the night or the whole night.
to cause (someone) to stay awake, to prevent someone from having his sleep.
to lack enough sleep; hence, to be sleepy.

PUYO.eng_example: The cake which I was baking puffed up.

PUYUPUY.definition: breeze, a gentle blow of the wind.
